-97]]}}\n{{medal|W|[[Ukrainian Top League]]| [[1997-98 Vyshcha Liha|1997-98]]}}\n{{medal|W|[[Ukrainian Top League]]| [[1998-99 Vyshcha Liha|1998-99]]}}\n{{medal|W|[[Ukrainian Top League]]| [[1999-2000 Vyshcha Liha|1999-00]]}}\n{{medal|W|[[Ukrainian Top League]]| [[2000-01 Vyshcha Liha|2000-01]]}}\n{{medal|W|[[Ukrainian Top League]]| [[2002-03 Vyshcha Liha|2002-03]]}}\n{{medal|W|[[Ukrainian Cup]]| [[1995-96 Ukrainian Cup|1995-96]]}}\n{{medal|W|[[Ukrainian Cup]]| [[1997-98 Ukrainian Cup|1997-98]]}}\n{{medal|W|[[Ukrainian Cup]]| [[1998-99 Ukrainian Cup|1998-99]]}}\n{{medal|W|[[Ukrainian Cup]]| [[1999-2000 Ukrainian Cup|1999-00]]}}\n{{medal|W|[[Ukrainian Cup]]| [[2002-03 Ukrainian Cup|2002-03]]}}\n}}\n\n'''Oleksandr Holovko''' ({{lang-uk|\u041e\u043b\u0435\u043a\u0441\u0430\u043d\u0434\u0440 \u0411\u043e\u0440\u0438\u0441\u043e\u0432\u0438\u0447 \u0413\u043e\u043b\u043e\u0432\u043a\u043e}}, born 6 January 1972 in [[Kherson]]) is a former [[Ukraine|Ukrainian]] [[football defender]] who last played for [[Tavriya Simferopol]], In his career, he played in the centre-back position.<ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.fourfourtwo.com/features/dynamo-kyiv-99-what-happened-next | title=Dynamo Kyiv '99: What happened next? | date=17 March 2011 | work=FourFourTwo | accessdate=15 April 2014 }}</ref> Holovko also used to be a regular start-up for the [[Ukrainian national football team]]. He earned eight national championship titles with two clubs.\n\n==Career==\nHolovko has played for three clubs, [[Tavriya Simferopol]], [[Dynamo Kyiv]] and [[Qingdao Beilaite]] (P.R. China). A top notch central or right defender, Holovko helped lead [[Dynamo Kyiv]] to many victories in the [[UEFA Champions League]], cumulating in a semifinal finish in 1998\u20131999. He was also a regular member of the [[Ukraine national football team]] from 1995 to 2004, having appeared in 58 international matches (among the cap leaders for Ukraine). As for playing his career, he stopped his career at the age 38.\n\nHolovko started as a coach of the Ukrainian Under 16 Youth National Team. The team competed in September 2008 for qualification to the 2009 UEFA U-17 Championships.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{NFT player|pid=6943}}\n* [http://www.fanatukr.com/igrok/holovko.html Profile on website Football Ukraine]\n\n{{Ukraine national under-21 football team managers}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Holovko, Oleksandr}}\n[[Category:Ukrainian footballers]]\n[[Category:Ukraine international footballers]]\n[[Category:Ukrainian Premier League players]]\n[[Category:FC Dynamo Kyiv players]]\n[[Category:SC Tavriya Simferopol players]]\n[[Category:People from Kherson]]\n[[Category:Ukrainian expatriate footballers]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in China]]\n[[Category:Qingdao Jonoon F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Chinese Super League players]]\n[[Category:1972 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Ukraine national under-21 football team managers]]\n[[Category:Association football defenders]]\n[[Category:Ukrainian football managers]]\n\n\n{{Ukraine-footy-defender-1970s-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{distinguish|Oleksandr Holovko (footballer, born 1995)}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2013}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Oleksandr Holovko\n| image = Oleksandr Holovko.jpeg\n| image_size = 200\n| fullname = Oleksandr Borysovych Holovko\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1972|1|6}}\n| birth_place = [[Kherson]], [[Ukrainian SSR]]\n| death_date =\n| height =\n| position = [[Centre back]]\n| currentclub = \n| youthyears1 = 1990\u20131993\n| youthclubs1 = [[SC Tavriya Simferopol|Tavriya Simferopol]]\n| years1 = 1992\u20131995\n| years2 = 1995\u20132004\n| years3 = 2004\n| years4 = 2004\u20132006\n| clubs1 = [[SC Tavriya Simferopol|Tavriya Simferopol]]\n| clubs2 = [[Dynamo Kyiv]]\n| clubs3 = [[Qingdao Jonoon F.C.|Qingdao Beilaite]]\n| clubs4 = [[SC Tavriya Simferopol|Tavriya Simferopol]]\n| caps1 = 108\n| caps2 = 230\n| caps3 = 19\n| caps4 = 32\n| goals1 = 3\n| 